Hmmmm

On one hand, I really like the time travel aspect (or perhaps it would be more accurate to call it reincarnation?) and how James Connolly has been basically been leading rebellions across history as this charismatic dynamo of unrest.

On the other hand, I think the SCP Foundation here is not played in character. I get that the sudden relaxation of 4000's containment is part of the effect, but you'd think way more people would be sounding alarms, even going off-site to notify different commanders that  If such communication was intercepted and the doubters silenced, I'd have an easier time believing how fast this escalated. As is, it looks like the Foundation is just plain ignorant.

I'm erring on the side of a +1. However, I feel if you fill the above gaps you'd have a much, much stronger SCP for it.







